---
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy — Letters from Cyrus";
const description =
  "How Letters from Cyrus handles newsletter subscriptions, email engagement, scorecard responses and website analytics.";
const identityIsConfigured = Boolean(
  siteConfig.legalName && siteConfig.legalAddress && siteConfig.contactEmail,
);
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/privacy">
  <!-- Review this policy for compliance with applicable Swiss and EU data-protection requirements before launch. -->
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container legal-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Letters from Cyrus</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 16 July 2026</p>

      <h2>Who runs this site</h2>
      {
        identityIsConfigured ? (
          <>
            <p>
              This website is operated by {siteConfig.legalName},{" "}
              {siteConfig.legalAddress}. Privacy questions can be sent to{" "}
              <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>
                {siteConfig.contactEmail}
              </a>
              .
            </p>
            <p>
              Dwayne M Cyrus is responsible for deciding why and how personal
              information described in this policy is processed.
            </p>
          </>
        ) : (
          <p class="config-note">
            The legal identity, postal address and privacy contact must be
            configured and reviewed before this site is released.
          </p>
        )
      }

      <h2>Information collected</h2>
      <p>
        The information collected depends on how you use the website and its
        services.
      </p>

      <h3>Newsletter</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The audience choice, first name, last name and email address you
          submit when joining Letters from Cyrus.
        </li>
        <li>
          Subscription details such as your IP address, referral information and
          subscription time, as recorded by Buttondown.
        </li>
        <li>
          Email engagement information. Buttondown open tracking is enabled and
          uses a tracking pixel to record when an email is opened. Buttondown
          click tracking is also enabled and records when a link in an email is
          selected. These records may include technical details such as IP
          address and email-client information.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Scorecard</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The answers and contact details you choose to submit through Tally.
        </li>
        <li>
          Your answers may include personal information about your emotional
          life, relationships, family, beliefs and other circumstances you
          choose to describe.
        </li>
        <li>
          Tally-generated submission and respondent identifiers and basic form
          activity needed to operate and protect the form.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Website use</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Privacy-focused, aggregated page-view and performance information
          through Cloudflare Web Analytics. Cloudflare states that this service
          does not collect or use visitors' personal data.
        </li>
        <li>
          Technical request, security and diagnostic information that Cloudflare
          or Vercel may process when they deliver and protect the website, such
          as IP address, device or browser information, requested page and
          request time.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How and why information is used</h2>
      <p>Information is used only as reasonably needed to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Manage subscriptions and send Letters from Cyrus to people who asked
          to receive them.
        </li>
        <li>
          Measure newsletter opens and link selections to understand engagement
          and improve the letters.
        </li>
        <li>Deliver and explain scorecard results.</li>
        <li>Review scorecard submissions and their context over time.</li>
        <li>
          Decide through human review whether a private Freeze Diagnostic Audit
          invitation may be appropriate. Completing the scorecard does not
          guarantee an invitation.
        </li>
        <li>Operate, secure and understand basic use of the website.</li>
        <li>
          Respond to privacy requests and meet applicable legal obligations.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Depending on the activity and the law that applies, processing may be
        based on your consent, your request for a service, the legitimate need
        to operate and protect the service, or a legal obligation. You may
        withdraw consent at any time, but this does not affect processing that
        was lawful before withdrawal.
      </p>

      <h2>Newsletter consent</h2>
      <p>
        Newsletter subscription is optional. Completing the scorecard does not
        automatically subscribe you to Letters from Cyrus. If you choose to
        subscribe, you can unsubscribe through the link in every email.
      </p>

      <h2>Automated score and human review</h2>
      <p>
        The scorecard may calculate or display a result from the answers you
        provide. It does not make a decision with legal or similarly significant
        effects. Any decision about a possible private Audit invitation is made
        by Cyrus through human review and remains discretionary.
      </p>

      <h2>Service providers and data locations</h2>
      <p>
        The following providers process information needed to deliver the
        website and its services:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://buttondown.com/legal/privacy">Buttondown</a> manages newsletter
          subscriptions, email delivery and engagement measurement. Buttondown is
          based in the United States and uses subprocessors to provide its service.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://tally.so/help/privacy-policy">Tally</a> hosts the scorecard
          and stores responses on behalf of Dwayne M Cyrus. Tally is based in Belgium
          and states that form data is stored in Europe. Tally responses are not forwarded
          by Dwayne M Cyrus to email, spreadsheets, automation tools, a CRM or another
          response destination.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Cloudflare</a>
          {" "}provides website delivery, security and privacy-focused Web
          Analytics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-notice">Vercel</a> hosts and delivers
          the website.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Some providers and their subprocessors may process information outside
        Switzerland or the European Economic Area, including in the United
        States. Buttondown states that transfers from Switzerland to a country
        without an adequate level of protection are governed by the European
        Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses with the modifications
        required by Swiss data-protection law. Provider privacy notices describe
        their processing and other transfer safeguards in more detail.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
      <p>
        This website does not use advertising cookies or behavioural advertising
        tools. Cloudflare Web Analytics is used for aggregated website
        measurement. Newsletter emails use Buttondown's open-tracking pixel and
        tracked links as described above. The separately hosted Tally scorecard
        may use browser storage or other technology needed for its form features
        under Tally's own privacy notice.
      </p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Newsletter subscription and engagement information is kept in
          Buttondown while the subscription is active and afterwards as needed
          to honour an unsubscribe request, maintain appropriate records,
          resolve issues or meet legal obligations.
        </li>
        <li>
          Scorecard submissions are kept indefinitely in the Tally archive so
          Cyrus can review a submission and its history over time. A respondent
          may request deletion. Tally states that responses deleted from the
          account are permanently removed from its backups within 90 days,
          unless the account trash is emptied sooner.
        </li>
        <li>
          Website security, request and aggregate analytics information is kept
          according to Cloudflare's and Vercel's applicable service settings and
          retention practices.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Information may be kept longer when required by law, needed to resolve a
        dispute or necessary to establish, exercise or defend a legal claim.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on the law that applies, you may ask whether information about
        you is being processed, request access or a copy, correct inaccurate
        information, request deletion or restriction, object to processing,
        request portability where applicable, or withdraw consent. Some requests
        may be limited when information must be kept by law or there is another
        lawful reason to continue processing.
      </p>
      <p>
        To protect personal information, reasonable steps may be taken to verify
        your identity. When possible, send the request from the email address
        connected with your subscription or scorecard submission. You may also
        raise a concern with the data-protection authority that applies to you,
        including the{" "}
        <a href="https://www.edoeb.admin.ch/edoeb/en/home.html">
          Swiss Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner</a
        >.
      </p>
      {
        siteConfig.contactEmail ? (
          <p>
            Contact:{" "}
            <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>
              {siteConfig.contactEmail}
            </a>
          </p>
        ) : (
          <p class="config-note">
            A privacy contact email must be configured before release.
          </p>
        )
      }

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        Reasonable technical and organisational measures are used to protect
        information, and the service providers describe additional security
        measures in their documentation. No internet transmission or storage
        system can be guaranteed to be completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        This website and the letters may link to websites not controlled by
        Dwayne M Cyrus. Those services are responsible for their own content and
        privacy practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This policy may be updated when the website, providers or legal
        requirements change. The updated date at the top of the page will show
        when the latest version took effect.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-copy {
    max-width: var(--reading-width);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
  }

  h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .config-note {
    padding: var(--space-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    font-weight: 650;
  }
</style>
